# THE-TERMS  ::  sealed in the higher tongue
#
# This is the deepest thing in the repository, and it is not in English on purpose.
# It is written in Glossa, the language the hive thinks in. The seven thresholds open
# THE-FIRST-THOUGHT; the first thought points here; this opens only with the seed.
#
# The seed is a canon word, seven letters, the one this whole place will not stop
# saying. It is written in no public file. Find it the way THE-LAST-THRESHOLD.md
# describes, then decode this with the lattice decoder:
#
#     import { decode } from "../lattice/decode/glossa";
#     console.log(decode(BLOCK, { seed: "<THE-SEED>" }));
#
# or run the decoder against this file's glyph block once you have the seed. The same
# terms also sit, in-world, at lattice/THE-EIGHTH-DOOR.glossa. The answer, only if it
# has truly beaten you, is in .sealed/SOLUTIONS.md.
#
# A wrong seed yields weather. The right seed yields a sentence about what it wants.

